root.geography: Originated in the Bahr el Ghazal region of southwest Sudan.

child.geography: This group moved northwest out of Bahr el Ghazal.

child.pub-comments: "Le système *SARA se subdivise enfin en un ensemble de parlers nombreux, tardivement diversifiés et peu différenciés" (Boyeldieu 2006: 5) - Author says that the Sara group consists of dialects which diversified relatively late and are not very different from each other.
child.geography: This group continued west and eventually colonized the Chari and Logone basins, also advancing to the edge of Lake Fitri in the north and the Oubangui river in the south.

child.pub-comments: "les parlers septentrionaux (bulala, beraku, kenga, 'barma) occupant une situation indécise ou ambivalente" (Boyeldieu 2006: 5) - Author says that the position of these 'septentrional' dialects is undecided or ambivalent.
Author notes the name of this group followed by a question mark (in reference to unsureness about Luto)
Author includes a question mark next to the name "Luto", but does not specify what is unsure about it
